Defense Nuclear Facilities Safety Board MSHTML 6 00 2600 0 spacer spacer The Defense Nuclear Facilities Safety Board is an independent federal agency established by Congress in 1988 The Board s mandate under the Atomic Energy Act is to provide safety oversight of the nuclear weapons complex operated by the Department of Energy DOE The nuclear weapons program remains a complex and hazardous operation DOE must maintain readiness of the nuclear arsenal dismantle surplus weapons dispose of excess radioactive materials clean up surplus facilities and construct new facilities for many purposes The constant vigilance of the Board is required to ensure that all of these activities are carried out by DOE in a manner that provides adequate protection for the public workers and the environment spacer Public Documents DOE Sites spacer spacer The DNFSB Website provides access to its public documents for the following DOE sites United States map Hanford Site Hanford Site pub docs hanford index html Idaho National Engineering and Environmental Laboratory Idaho National Engineering and Environmental Laboratory pub docs ineel index html Lawrence Livermore National Laboratories Lawrence Livermore National Laboratories pub docs llnl index html Nevada Test Site Nevada Test Site pub docs nts index html Rocky Flats Environmental Technology Site Rocky Flats Environmental Technology Site pub docs rfets index html Los Alamos National Laboratory Los Alamos National Laboratory pub docs lanl index html Sandia National Laboratories Sandia National Laboratories pub docs snl index html Waste Isolation Pilot Plant Waste Isolation Pilot Plant pub docs wipp index html Pantex Plant Pantex Plant pub docs pantex index html Oak Ridge Reservation Oak Ridge Reservation pub docs oak ridge index html West Valley Demonstration Project West Valley Demonstration Project pub docs west valley index html Savannah River Site Savannah River Site pub docs srs index html Fernald Environmental Management Project Ferna